Indonesia Stocks: Bumi, Energi Mega, Hexindo Adiperkasa, Timah

-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 
2011-06-13T09:30:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-13/indonesia-stocks-aneka-tambang-energi-mega-persada-timah.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the 4 p.m. Jakarta-time close.  The  Jakarta Composite index (JCI)  declined 38.89 points, or 1
percent, to 3,748.76, the steepest drop since May 23.  Energy companies: PT Energi Mega Persada (ENRG IJ), the
nation’s second-largest listed oil company, fell 3.4 percent to
198 rupiah, the steepest drop since May 23. PT Benakat Petroleum
Energy (BIPI IJ) lost 3.3 percent to 117 rupiah.  Crude oil for July delivery sank the most in four weeks on
June 10, losing 2.6 percent to $99.29 a barrel in  New York . The
contract decreased 1 percent to $98.29 today.  PT Bumi Resources (BUMI IJ), Indonesia’s largest coal
producer, fell 2.9 percent to 3,325 rupiah. The shares declined
as the sale of a mining unit, PT Bumi Resources Minerals, to
Vallar Plc in return for convertible bonds raised questions
about the deal’s financial impact on the company, according to
Bagus Hananto, an analyst at PT Onix Capital.  PT Hexindo Adiperkasa (HEXA IJ), the Indonesian unit of
Hitachi Construction Machinery Co., dropped 1.6 percent to 6,200
rupiah, the most since May 25. The company had its share-price
estimate cut to 8,900 rupiah from 9,500 rupiah by Arief Budiman,
an analyst at PT OSK Nusadana Securities  Indonesia , because of
“weak” sales volume in April and May.  PT Timah (TINS IJ), Indonesia’s largest tin producer, fell
2 percent to 2,500 rupiah, the lowest close since March 22. Tin
futures lost 1.4 percent to $25,350 a metric ton in  London  on
June 10, completing an eighth straight weekly decline.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
 bmoestafa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
